  "prompt": "Why we are always haunted by the idea that we are wasting our life?",
  "response": "This persistent feeling of potentially wasting life stems from several psychological and existential factors:\n\n1. Existential Anxiety\n- Awareness of mortality\n- Limited time and finite human lifespan\n- Fear of not fulfilling potential\n- Pressure to create meaningful experiences\n\n2. Social Comparison\n- Constant exposure to others' achievements through social media\n- Unrealistic expectations of success\n- Feeling behind or inadequate compared to peers\n- Internalized societal standards of success\n\n3. Psychological Factors\n- Natural human tendency towards self-doubt\n- Fear of regret\n- Uncertainty about life choices\n- Perfectionism and high self-expectations\n\n4. Cultural Influences\n- Productivity-driven societal values\n- Capitalist emphasis on achievement\n- Narrow definitions of success\n- Constant pressure to be \"doing something\"\n\n5. Deeper Philosophical Reasons\n- Inherent human desire for meaning\n- Consciousness of our own potential\n- Awareness of life's complexity\n- Struggle between individual aspirations and external expectations\n\n6. Neurological Perspective\n- Evolutionary survival mechanism\n- Brain's tendency to focus on potential risks and unfulfilled goals\n- Constant self-evaluation as a survival strategy\n\nUnderstanding these factors can help develop a more balanced, compassionate perspective towards oneself and one's life journey.",
